	<main>
		<header class="header goal-3">
			<h1>Sustainable Consumption and Production</h1>
			<p>
				Protect life on land by promoting sustainable forest management, halting biodiversity loss, and combating
				desertification.
			</p>
		</header>
		<main class="content">
			<div class="related-topics">
				<h3>Related Topics:</h3>
				<div class="dropdown">
					<details class="dropdown-details">
						<summary>Chemicals and waste</summary>
						<p>
							Reducing harmful chemicals and waste is crucial to protecting biodiversity. Proper disposal and
							sustainable alternatives help prevent contamination of ecosystems and groundwater, ensuring
							healthier environments for both humans and wildlife.
						</p>
					</details>
					<details class="dropdown-details">
						<summary>Sustainable forest management</summary>
						<p>
							Sustainable forest management involves practices that maintain the health and productivity of
							forests while supporting the needs of local communities and economies. It includes reforestation,
							selective logging, and protecting old-growth forests to preserve biodiversity.
						</p>
					</details>
					<details class="dropdown-details">
						<summary>Wildlife protection</summary>
						<p>
							Safeguarding wildlife is essential for maintaining ecological balance. Efforts such as creating
							protected habitats, preventing poaching, and mitigating human-wildlife conflicts contribute to
							preserving species and their roles in ecosystems.
						</p>
					</details>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="overview">
				<h3>Overview:</h3>
				<p>
					This goal focuses on preserving biodiversity, sustainable forest management, and reversing land
					degradation caused by desertification. Protecting ecosystems is essential for mitigating climate change
					and ensuring the survival of countless species.
				</p>
			</div>
